curam.util.ctm.bom.event.impl

Class EventReadAndUpsertBOMImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.ctm.bom.BusinessObjectModuleImpl
      • curam.util.ctm.bom.event.impl.EventReadAndUpsertBOMImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BusinessObjectModule, ReadAndUpsertBOM

    public class EventReadAndUpsertBOMImpl
extends BusinessObjectModuleImpl
implements ReadAndUpsertBOM
    This class is responsible for reading, updating and inserting Event BOM information. An Event BOM consists of an Event class record and it's associated Event type records.

      • convertBusinessObjectContentToXML

        public org.w3c.dom.Document convertBusinessObjectContentToXML(BusinessObjectIdentifier boIdentifier)
                                                       throws AppException,
                                                              InformationalException
        This method takes in an eventClass as the key for the Event BOM, and uses this key to retrieve the EventClass record and it's associated EventType records for this BOM. All of this information is then stored in XML format as specified by the BOM infrastructure.
        Specified by:
        convertBusinessObjectContentToXML in interface ReadAndUpsertBOM
        Parameters:
        boIdentifier - The key for an Event BOM.
        Returns:
        An XML representation of the specified Event BOM as outlined by the BOM infrastructure.
        Throws:
        AppException - Exceptions that may be thrown when creating the XML for the specified Event BOM.
        InformationalException - Generic Exception Signature.

      • upsertEventClassEntity

        public void upsertEventClassEntity(java.lang.Object entityDtlsObj)
                            throws AppException,
                                   InformationalException
        This method inserts or updates an EventClass record. The processing that occurs depends on the whether the EventClass being transported is already available in the target system or not.

        If the EventClass being transported, is not available in the target system, a new record is inserted. If the EventClass being transported, is already available in the target system, the existing record is not modified as there is no modification required.

        Parameters:
        entityDtlsObj - The EventClass details to insert or update.
        Throws:
        AppException - Generic Exception Signature.
        InformationalException - Generic Exception Signature.
